<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4651> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4651" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Active in moving to send successors to the provinces of Lucullus (Plut. Luc. 33.5; cf. Sall. Hist. 4.71 M)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4650> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4650" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "6 Tribune of the Plebs in 74. His activity in the praetorship must have begun before Cilicia was taken from Lucullus, most probably upon receipt of news of the campaign of 69." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4559> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4559" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commander of cavalry under Crassus against Spartacus (Frontin. Str. 2.5.23; cf. Plut. Crass. 11.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4414> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4414" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His agitation for restoration of the powers of the tribunate was checked by Lucullus (Cic. Cluent. 110-112; Sall. Hist. 3.48.11M; Plut. Luc. 5.4; Ps.-Ascon. 189 Stangl). Defended Oppianicus, and after his condemnation secured the conviction of C. Iunius, the Iudex Quaestionis, and prosecuted Falcula, one of the jurors (Cic. Cluent. 72-96, 103-116 passim, 119, 136-138, 178; Verr. 1.29; 2.1.157; Quintil. Inst. Or. 5.13.39; Ps.-Ascon. 206, 216, and 255f. Stangl; Schol. Gron. 328, and 351 Stangl; Schol. on Pers. Sat. 2.19)." .
